#20655
Entrance to House DaenVilae~
The entrance to the house is humble by drow standards, save for the
jeweled statues of the Spider Queen that seem to form a ring around this
place.  The courtyard is filled with many drow talking in hushed tones,
almost as if they are revealing the secrets of the underworld to another. 
The soft hum of magic fills the air along with the magical glow of faerie
fire that lines the stone building.  The building is somewhat crude due to
its natural state, being that it has been untouched by drow sculptors.  The
inside of the house, which lies to the south, appears to be filled with many
pictures.  A city street lies to the north.
~
