#20656
The Throne Room of House DaenVilae~
The throne room of the city's third house is decorated just as the inner
courtyard is.  A few lavish velvet tapestries hang from the ceiling,
emblazoned with a spider wielding a weapon in each leg, the symbol of the
House DaenVilae.  A blood-covered altar rests in the center of the room,
before a humble throne covered in ebony satin and silks.  No light permeates
this place save for a singular candle that burns above the throne, casting a
glow upon a horrific statue of a half-drow, half-spider creature.  The
Spider Queen's presence is strong within this place, keeping the house under
her divine protection.  The only exit from this place is to the north, into
the heart of the house.
~
